1
00:01:56,799 --> 00:01:57,700
Ms. Liu, morning.

2
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,760
That's too old-fashioned. That won't do.

3
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:06,659
Ms. Liu.

4
00:02:07,019 --> 00:02:08,180
Have you eaten yet?

5
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:09,599
That's even more cliché.

6
00:02:12,060 --> 00:02:12,860
Hello.

7
00:02:13,659 --> 00:02:14,500
Ms. Liu.

8
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,340
Boss Li.

9
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:19,800
Every single day,

10
00:02:19,819 --> 00:02:21,740
I see you exercising early in the morning.

11
00:02:21,759 --> 00:02:23,219
Your body is really strong.

12
00:02:23,819 --> 00:02:24,939
Pity your eyesight isn't great.

13
00:02:24,939 --> 00:02:26,439
You mistook me for Ms. Liu.

14
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:27,800
We do look a bit alike.

15
00:02:27,979 --> 00:02:28,740
I took you for...

16
00:02:30,599 --> 00:02:32,379
My eyesight really is terrible.

17
00:02:32,599 --> 00:02:33,259
It's okay.

18
00:02:33,259 --> 00:02:33,819
It doesn't matter.

19
00:02:34,580 --> 00:02:36,180
Bad eyesight doesn't matter either.

20
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:37,120
Later I'll get you...

21
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:39,139
...some sheep liver to nourish your eyes.

22
00:02:39,139 --> 00:02:40,060
Thanks.

23
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,379
I don't eat sheep liver.

24
00:02:41,379 --> 00:02:42,460
You don't like sheep liver?

25
00:02:42,460 --> 00:02:43,479
That doesn't matter either.

26
00:02:43,479 --> 00:02:44,539
I can switch it to chicken liver for you.

27
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,900
Or else pig liver.

28
00:02:46,219 --> 00:02:47,060
If that doesn't work...

29
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:48,960
Chicken liver, sheep liver, pig liver all together...

30
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,560
...boiled in a pot, chopped up, and mixed with rice for you.

31
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:52,620
For you.

32
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,159
Are you feeding a cat?

33
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,539
You...

34
00:02:55,539 --> 00:02:57,219
Fine.

35
00:02:57,379 --> 00:02:58,080
Xiao Cai.

36
00:02:59,719 --> 00:03:01,539
Buy whatever liver you want.

37
00:03:02,099 --> 00:03:03,639
Even if you buy a bamboo pole...

38
00:03:03,639 --> 00:03:04,840
...I'll eat that too, okay?

39
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:06,620
As long as you leave first.

40
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:07,699
Don't hold me up.

41
00:03:09,199 --> 00:03:10,639
Practicing boxing.

42
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:13,020
Why don't you go outside to practice?

43
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:14,159
Everyone loves to gossip.

44
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:16,979
I'm leaving.

45
00:03:26,719 --> 00:03:27,860
Boss Li, morning.

46
00:03:28,659 --> 00:03:29,180
Morning.

47
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:31,020
All that buildup for nothing.

48
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,800
What style of boxing are you practicing?

49
00:03:33,819 --> 00:03:34,500
This is...

50
00:03:34,759 --> 00:03:36,900
...authentic Chinese boxing.

51
00:03:37,439 --> 00:03:38,400
Tai Chi.

52
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,280
Tai Chi.

53
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,000
I have a Tai Chi Sword.

54
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:43,560
What a coincidence.

55
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,719
I knew it.

56
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:47,360
We have a lot in common.

57
00:03:47,439 --> 00:03:49,199
We often do the same things without planning.

58
00:03:50,039 --> 00:03:51,879
Fine, you practice your boxing here.

59
00:03:51,879 --> 00:03:52,960
I'll go practice at the entrance.

60
00:03:52,979 --> 00:03:53,699
Don't.

61
00:03:54,719 --> 00:03:56,800
I mean your suggestion is excellent.

62
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,680
Let's go practice together outside.

63
00:03:59,419 --> 00:04:00,520
Did I suggest that?

64
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:02,240
I'm practicing sword.

65
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,599
You're practicing boxing.

66
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,319
Mine is Tai Chi Sword.

67
00:04:05,319 --> 00:04:06,240
Yes.

68
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:07,840
You practice Tai Chi Sword.

69
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,960
I practice Tai Chi.

70
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,000
If we go outside, people will see...

71
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,080
...how well-matched these two are.

72
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,120
No.

73
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,600
I mean the chemistry.

74
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:17,839
That's not it either.

75
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:19,560
Anyway, people will look and see...

76
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:21,199
...a matching pair.

77
00:04:33,759 --> 00:04:37,199
We workers have strength!

78
00:04:37,759 --> 00:04:39,680
We workers have strength!

79
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:42,899
The Professor won't get up in the morning!

80
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,480
The Professor won't get up in the morning!

81
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,560
I'm feeling unwell.

82
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:49,439
What are you saying?

83
00:04:50,319 --> 00:04:51,720
I asked why you haven't got up yet.

84
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:54,339
I don't feel well.

85
00:04:54,579 --> 00:04:55,740
I have a fever.

86
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:57,899
You have a fever?

87
00:05:07,379 --> 00:05:08,220
You're really burning up.

88
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,579
This...

89
00:05:10,259 --> 00:05:11,740
Tell me, what should we do?

90
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:15,779
When you're old, your immunity is weak.

91
00:05:16,220 --> 00:05:16,899
Once you get a fever,

92
00:05:17,199 --> 00:05:18,699
it might trigger other problems.

93
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:20,220
What on earth should we do?

94
00:05:21,620 --> 00:05:22,259
Old Fan,

95
00:05:22,420 --> 00:05:23,379
you have to hang in there.

96
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,180
I'll go get a volunteer for you.

97
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,579
Okay. You must hang in there.

98
00:05:28,019 --> 00:05:29,139
Persistence is victory!

99
00:05:29,139 --> 00:05:29,779
Okay.

100
00:05:30,420 --> 00:05:31,660
Victory belongs to you!

101
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:32,300
Fine.

102
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,019
You really have to hang in there!

103
00:05:34,019 --> 00:05:35,220
Are you going or not?

104
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:37,500
If you keep fussing, I won't make it.

105
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,220
Darn it!

106
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:40,199
Hanyū Eiko!

107
00:05:40,199 --> 00:05:41,220
Help!

108
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:43,459
Old Fan is dying!

109
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,500
It's nothing.

110
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,120
It's no big deal.

111
00:05:51,959 --> 00:05:53,040
No need to worry.

112
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,639
It is simply...

113
00:05:54,959 --> 00:05:56,000
External invasion of pathogenic wind,

114
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,199
internal damp-heat,

115
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,600
exuberant liver fire,

116
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,600
and deficient lung qi.

117
00:06:01,399 --> 00:06:02,319
Do you understand "deficient lung qi"?

118
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:02,959
I understand.

119
00:06:03,959 --> 00:06:05,079
What do I understand?

120
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:06,480
Just tell us what the illness is.

121
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,120
Right.

122
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:08,899
Use medical language

123
00:06:08,899 --> 00:06:10,959
that you can understand.

124
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:12,699
He just caught a chill.

125
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:15,000
Is it just a common cold?

126
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,360
A vulgar way to put it.

127
00:06:18,279 --> 00:06:19,439
But I suppose you could say that.

128
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:21,839
However...

129
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:24,680
You must not take it lightly.

130
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:25,879
You must...

131
00:06:25,879 --> 00:06:29,040
take these three medicines I prescribed on time.

132
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,279
Three times a day.

133
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:32,980
Guaranteed to cure the illness.

134
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:34,019
Okay.

135
00:06:34,220 --> 00:06:34,740
Alright?

136
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:36,019
Understood.

137
00:06:37,899 --> 00:06:38,579
Doctor.

138
00:06:39,139 --> 00:06:40,980
Is this a decoction or pills?

139
00:06:41,779 --> 00:06:43,300
Isn't this just cold capsules?

140
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,339
What did you expect?

141
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,480
But this medicine is really effective.

142
00:06:48,519 --> 00:06:50,540
By the way, the patient...

143
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:52,579
needs someone dedicated to nursing him.

144
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:54,699
To prevent him from kicking off the covers when sweating.

145
00:06:55,019 --> 00:06:56,339
How about I do it?

146
00:06:57,139 --> 00:06:58,220
But I'm a girl.

147
00:06:58,220 --> 00:06:59,379
Would it be inconvenient?

148
00:06:59,660 --> 00:07:00,579
Let me do it.

149
00:07:00,579 --> 00:07:02,139
I can make do on the sofa for a while.

150
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,180
I can handle this.

151
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,540
I was a doctor when I was in the army.

152
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:08,540
Often staying up all night.

153
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:09,420
Working through the night.

154
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:09,860
Boss Li.

155
00:07:10,379 --> 00:07:12,740
You were a medic back then, right?

156
00:07:12,740 --> 00:07:13,420
Who?

157
00:07:13,459 --> 00:07:14,379
Who was a medic?

158
00:07:14,660 --> 00:07:16,019
I was a vet.

159
00:07:16,259 --> 00:07:17,740
I often nursed sick pigs.

160
00:07:17,939 --> 00:07:19,019
Stop right there.

161
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:20,740
Lest the patient hears you.

162
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:22,019
And gets agitated.

163
00:07:22,339 --> 00:07:23,019
Why?

164
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,939
Treating people or pigs is all about saving lives.

165
00:07:26,139 --> 00:07:26,980
As long as it's work...

166
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:28,500
I never pick and choose.

167
00:07:28,779 --> 00:07:29,720
Even a skinny pig, I...

168
00:07:29,779 --> 00:07:30,360
Okay.

169
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:30,980
Boss Li.

170
00:07:31,579 --> 00:07:32,420
That's enough.

171
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:33,899
I think...

172
00:07:35,439 --> 00:07:36,500
I should do it.

173
00:07:36,660 --> 00:07:37,339
No way.

174
00:07:37,339 --> 00:07:38,100
That's not good.

175
00:07:38,639 --> 00:07:40,180
How can we let a great artist...

176
00:07:40,180 --> 00:07:41,339
do this?

177
00:07:41,639 --> 00:07:42,639
What if he...

178
00:07:42,639 --> 00:07:43,540
vomits on the floor or soils the bed?

179
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,939
What would you do then?

180
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,100
Let me do it.

181
00:07:46,139 --> 00:07:47,220
In the army...

182
00:07:47,220 --> 00:07:48,220
I fed pigs.

183
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,180
Feeding him now...

184
00:07:49,339 --> 00:07:50,699
the Professor is about the same.

185
00:07:51,139 --> 00:07:52,540
How can that be the same?

186
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:53,819
Alright, say no more.

187
00:07:53,819 --> 00:07:54,379
I'll do it.

188
00:08:09,339 --> 00:08:10,139
Ms. Liu.

189
00:08:10,579 --> 00:08:12,259
When I was a vet back then...

190
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,899
it was also mouthful by mouthful...

191
00:08:13,899 --> 00:08:15,300
feeding water to piglets.

192
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:17,420
But back then...

193
00:08:17,420 --> 00:08:18,699
I did some technical innovation.

194
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:20,259
I came up with a clever method.

195
00:08:20,259 --> 00:08:21,160
I and the doctor...

196
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:22,819
Boss Li.

197
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:25,259
Keep your voice down.

198
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:27,660
The patient needs quiet.

199
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:29,199
Needs quiet.

200
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,379
Otherwise...

201
00:08:30,819 --> 00:08:32,460
let's let him rest here quietly first.

202
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:33,700
Let's go out for a walk, the two of us.

203
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,580
And study Tai Chi and Tai Chi Sword.

204
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:39,580
Professor Fan

205
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:40,419
I'm really sorry

206
00:08:40,419 --> 00:08:41,820
Did I wake you up?

207
00:08:41,820 --> 00:08:43,659
Actually, I wasn't asleep

208
00:08:44,779 --> 00:08:45,620
You weren't asleep?

209
00:08:45,620 --> 00:08:46,259
Here

210
00:08:47,059 --> 00:08:48,299
Drink some water

211
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,159
That's enough

212
00:08:52,159 --> 00:08:52,960
That's about enough

213
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,039
Don't drink so much water

214
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:55,240
Drink too much and you'll wet the bed

215
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,659
He needs to drink plenty of water right now

216
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:58,960
To bring down the fever

217
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,080
To help him sweat

218
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:02,399
That drains a lot of fluids from the body

219
00:09:02,399 --> 00:09:03,840
So you have to drink more water

220
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,360
You need to replenish it in time

221
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:07,559
Sorry, sorry

222
00:09:07,559 --> 00:09:08,299
It's okay, it's okay

223
00:09:08,299 --> 00:09:08,879
Is it that you...

224
00:09:08,879 --> 00:09:09,919
...are uncomfortable sitting like this?

225
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:10,740
Here

226
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:11,299
Come on

227
00:09:11,299 --> 00:09:12,320
Hurry, come sit up

228
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:12,720
Sit up

229
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,279
Sit up and drink

230
00:09:14,340 --> 00:09:15,320
Ms. Liu, don't

231
00:09:15,659 --> 00:09:16,759
Don't do that, Ms. Liu, you...

232
00:09:16,759 --> 00:09:18,700
Don't

233
00:09:19,419 --> 00:09:21,019
What's wrong? Don't what?

234
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:23,500
Don't drink so much water

235
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:25,860
Drinking too much water isn't good either

236
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:27,580
We just changed the water barrel yesterday

237
00:09:27,779 --> 00:09:29,220
And today it's already hitting the bottom

238
00:09:29,539 --> 00:09:31,539
Isn't that for his immune system?

239
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,179
Before the immune system kicks in

240
00:09:33,179 --> 00:09:34,740
The urinary system will collapse first

241
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:36,860
Yeah

242
00:09:37,419 --> 00:09:38,620
That makes sense

243
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:39,460
Makes sense, right?

244
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:39,700
Yes

245
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:40,899
Listen to me

246
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:42,340
Just let him sleep here

247
00:09:42,379 --> 00:09:44,419
Let's go outside and study Tai Chi

248
00:09:44,419 --> 00:09:45,259
I won't sleep

249
00:09:45,820 --> 00:09:46,940
I can't sleep

250
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:49,259
Unless...

251
00:09:49,940 --> 00:09:51,659
Ms. Liu, you tell me a story

252
00:09:52,519 --> 00:09:54,080
When I was sick as a child

253
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:55,919
My mom would tell me stories

254
00:09:57,519 --> 00:09:58,320
Alright then

255
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:58,700
No

256
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,340
You even want Ms. Liu to tell you a story?

257
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:02,000
Keep it down

258
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,279
Telling stories, right?

259
00:10:03,279 --> 00:10:04,879
Telling stories is my strong suit

260
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:05,679
I'll tell you one

261
00:10:05,679 --> 00:10:06,120
Boss Li

262
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,759
I'll tell you a ghost story. From Liaozhai

263
00:10:08,139 --> 00:10:08,759
No

264
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:11,000
I want the childhood...

265
00:10:11,159 --> 00:10:12,240
...feeling of a mother

266
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:14,600
A ghost story?

267
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:15,360
You...

268
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,580
You look just like the King of Hell

269
00:10:17,639 --> 00:10:18,620
I'm scared looking at you

270
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:20,000
Who looks like the King of Hell?

271
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,740
That's enough, Boss Li

272
00:10:23,659 --> 00:10:24,899
Right now, the patient...

273
00:10:25,059 --> 00:10:26,659
...whether physically or mentally...

274
00:10:26,659 --> 00:10:28,059
...is at his weakest

275
00:10:28,059 --> 00:10:28,759
Listen

276
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,899
You have to follow his wishes

277
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:33,159
If we're following my wishes...

278
00:10:34,299 --> 00:10:35,659
Please ask him to leave now

279
00:10:35,940 --> 00:10:36,740
Why should I leave?

280
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:37,379
Fine

281
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:38,159
Alright

282
00:10:38,159 --> 00:10:38,700
Okay

283
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:39,580
Fine, I'll endure it

284
00:10:39,580 --> 00:10:40,379
I'll endure it

285
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,139
I'll just sit right here

286
00:10:42,419 --> 00:10:43,299
And not say a word

287
00:10:43,299 --> 00:10:44,100
Is that okay?

288
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,659
Good

289
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,720
Okay

290
00:10:49,299 --> 00:10:50,120
Then let's...

291
00:10:53,379 --> 00:10:54,179
Professor

292
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:56,659
Let's tell a story

293
00:10:58,019 --> 00:10:59,740
Tell a story just like Mom

294
00:11:03,299 --> 00:11:04,539
Once upon a time,

295
00:11:04,679 --> 00:11:05,360
there was a mountain.

296
00:11:08,659 --> 00:11:09,159
Right.

297
00:11:09,679 --> 00:11:10,639
There was a mountain.

298
00:11:11,799 --> 00:11:12,960
And on this mountain,

299
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:13,799
there was also a temple.

300
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:16,639
Can you stop messing around?

301
00:11:16,639 --> 00:11:17,779
How am I messing around?

302
00:11:17,919 --> 00:11:18,779
Ask Ms. Liu.

303
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,340
Is what I said true or not?

304
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:21,500
Is there a temple on the mountain?

305
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:21,700
Yes.

306
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:22,580
Let me think...

307
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:23,059
Well...

308
00:11:23,059 --> 00:11:23,820
Once upon a time, there was a mountain.

309
00:11:23,820 --> 00:11:24,379
On the mountain...

310
00:11:24,379 --> 00:11:24,740
Right.

311
00:11:24,740 --> 00:11:25,740
Yes, there was a temple on the mountain.

312
00:11:25,740 --> 00:11:26,539
I know the rest too.

313
00:11:26,539 --> 00:11:27,620
Not only was there a temple on the mountain,

314
00:11:27,899 --> 00:11:29,240
there was also a little demon that ate people.

315
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,039
Eating people wasn't enough,

316
00:11:30,039 --> 00:11:30,879
it wanted to eat a professor too.

317
00:11:30,919 --> 00:11:32,059
Don't... Let me tell you...

318
00:11:32,059 --> 00:11:33,480
That demon specifically eats professors.

319
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,659
Specifically professors named Fan.

320
00:11:34,759 --> 00:11:36,240
It eats them bite by bite, just like this.

321
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:40,299
Boss Li!

322
00:11:40,299 --> 00:11:42,019
I'm scared, so scared.

323
00:11:42,019 --> 00:11:43,120
Don't be scared, don't be scared.

324
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,799
Boss Li, what are you doing?

325
00:11:44,899 --> 00:11:46,419
Why are you always making trouble here?

326
00:11:46,419 --> 00:11:47,139
I'm just...

327
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:48,659
Look at you.

328
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:49,740
You... this...

329
00:11:49,899 --> 00:11:51,059
It just so happens to be lunchtime.

330
00:11:51,059 --> 00:11:52,019
How about this?

331
00:11:52,019 --> 00:11:53,899
You go to the canteen and get some food.

332
00:11:54,059 --> 00:11:54,620
You're hungry?

333
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:54,980
No.

334
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:55,620
What would you like to eat?

335
00:11:55,620 --> 00:11:56,080
No...

336
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,580
It doesn't matter for me.

337
00:11:57,659 --> 00:11:58,740
The key is the Professor.

338
00:11:58,740 --> 00:12:00,019
He is physically weak right now.

339
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:01,580
He must eat on time.

340
00:12:01,779 --> 00:12:03,259
Didn't the imperial physician say so?

341
00:12:03,539 --> 00:12:05,100
It's best to eat something bland.

342
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:06,580
A liquid diet is best.

343
00:12:06,580 --> 00:12:08,100
Anyway, you figure it out.

344
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,419
Actually, right now...

345
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:11,460
get my food as well.

346
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,179
Okay?

347
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:13,700
That works too.

348
00:12:14,659 --> 00:12:16,059
I'll get your food while I'm at it.

349
00:12:16,419 --> 00:12:16,940
Old Fan.

350
00:12:17,259 --> 00:12:18,340
Sleep well here.

351
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:20,100
Protect the doctor well.

352
00:12:20,139 --> 00:12:20,940
Don't move around.

353
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:23,100
Whatever you do, don't leave.

354
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:25,539
Old Sun is off!

355
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:31,500
Ms. Liu

356
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,679
First, I want to thank you for taking such good care of me.

357
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:37,039
You're too kind.

358
00:12:37,039 --> 00:12:38,919
It's the least I could do.

359
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:41,539
A close neighbor is better than a distant relative.

360
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:42,480
Right?

361
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:44,200
We should take care of each other.

362
00:12:45,559 --> 00:12:46,440
Besides,

363
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:47,919
for example, if I got sick,

364
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,039
wouldn't you

365
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,639
also take care of me

366
00:12:50,799 --> 00:12:52,039
the way I did for you?

367
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,440
That's for sure.

368
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,139
Exactly.

369
00:12:54,139 --> 00:12:56,279
I'd definitely be attentive and considerate.

370
00:12:56,879 --> 00:12:57,539
No,

371
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:58,960
Xiao Liu,

372
00:12:59,559 --> 00:13:01,399
I won't let you say things like that.

373
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,200
You will never get sick.

374
00:13:04,679 --> 00:13:06,039
But don't worry,

375
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,240
even if

376
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:08,440
you don't get sick,

377
00:13:08,639 --> 00:13:10,779
I'll still be attentive and considerate.

378
00:13:11,419 --> 00:13:12,220
Professor,

379
00:13:13,519 --> 00:13:14,600
Professor, just sit tight.

380
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,120
Well,

381
00:13:17,039 --> 00:13:18,440
us seniors

382
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,000
caring for each other,

383
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,639
looking after each other,

384
00:13:21,639 --> 00:13:22,720
is only right and proper.

385
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,220
Yes.

386
00:13:23,639 --> 00:13:24,840
Especially you.

387
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,759
You're learned and talented,

388
00:13:26,879 --> 00:13:28,200
and highly respected.

389
00:13:28,659 --> 00:13:31,019
You've dedicated your life's work and talent

390
00:13:31,139 --> 00:13:33,299
to the next generation.

391
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:37,000
I've always admired,

392
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,080
admired you the most,

393
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,039
as an intellectual.

394
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:45,500
Really?

395
00:13:48,419 --> 00:13:49,220
Ms. Liu,

396
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:51,639
is that really how you see me?

397
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,059
How come I usually

398
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,679
just didn't realize it?

399
00:13:58,379 --> 00:13:59,580
I was too slow.

400
00:13:59,779 --> 00:14:00,539
Too muddled.

401
00:14:00,539 --> 00:14:01,700
Too careless.

402
00:14:02,299 --> 00:14:03,480
But it's not too late now.

403
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:05,320
We can start over.

404
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:07,080
I'm back.

405
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:08,639
You're back so soon.

406
00:14:08,919 --> 00:14:09,259
Boss Li.

407
00:14:09,259 --> 00:14:10,039
Isn't it a coincidence?

408
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:12,360
I ran into Zhu Zhu and Xiao Xin on the way.

409
00:14:12,799 --> 00:14:14,320
They were going to get food for Grandma Jin.

410
00:14:14,679 --> 00:14:16,639
So I entrusted them to get the food.

411
00:14:17,039 --> 00:14:18,600
We can't let a small thing like getting food

412
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:20,039
interfere with taking care of the patient.

413
00:14:20,039 --> 00:14:21,120
It's such a big matter.

414
00:14:21,279 --> 00:14:23,399
Taking care of me isn't a big deal.

415
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,759
You ruined my big plan.

416
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:25,559
What big plan?

417
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,480
I just wanted to ask,

418
00:14:28,559 --> 00:14:30,139
what did you buy for me to eat?

419
00:14:30,279 --> 00:14:31,919
Cornmeal porridge, shredded pickles,

420
00:14:32,279 --> 00:14:33,600
and half a plate of radish leaves.

421
00:14:34,399 --> 00:14:35,399
Keep it light.

422
00:14:35,559 --> 00:14:36,960
You're feeding a rabbit, aren't you?

423
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,840
Isn't this abusing the patient?

424
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:40,179
I beg you,

425
00:14:40,419 --> 00:14:41,559
right now, immediately,

426
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:44,000
go buy me some pig trotters and ribs.

427
00:14:44,399 --> 00:14:45,759
Stewed offal, stir-fried liver.

428
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,039
If they don't have those,

429
00:14:47,279 --> 00:14:48,840
gristly meat, anything will do.

430
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,000
I want to eat meat.

431
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:50,759
Go quickly, okay?

432
00:14:50,759 --> 00:14:52,960
Where am I supposed to find those things for you?

433
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:53,759
Besides,

434
00:14:53,759 --> 00:14:55,320
your stomach and spleen are weak right now.

435
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,759
You can't eat those things anyway.

436
00:14:56,759 --> 00:14:57,840
You can't eat rich fish and meat.

437
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:58,720
Right, Ms. Liu?

438
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,360
Right.

439
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,720
He has to eat something light.

440
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:01,320
Right.

441
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:02,039
I agree.

442
00:15:02,039 --> 00:15:02,620
Can't eat it.

443
00:15:02,759 --> 00:15:04,039
Absolutely no rich fish and meat.

444
00:15:04,039 --> 00:15:04,600
But I...

445
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:05,480
However,

446
00:15:06,799 --> 00:15:08,200
eating a moderate amount,

447
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,360
for example, something low in cholesterol

448
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,679
and high in nutritional value,

449
00:15:10,879 --> 00:15:12,159
is still okay.

450
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:13,059
How about this?

451
00:15:13,179 --> 00:15:15,379
I'll go to the cafeteria myself to take a look.

452
00:15:15,379 --> 00:15:16,019
That's good.

453
00:15:16,019 --> 00:15:16,659
You go ahead.

454
00:15:16,659 --> 00:15:17,419
I'll take care of Old Fan.

455
00:15:17,419 --> 00:15:18,100
No need.

456
00:15:18,659 --> 00:15:19,860
I want Ms. Liu.

457
00:15:20,019 --> 00:15:20,700
No need for that.

458
00:15:21,179 --> 00:15:22,460
Then I'll go with Ms. Liu.

459
00:15:22,460 --> 00:15:23,179
The things are heavy.

460
00:15:23,179 --> 00:15:24,220
Come, I'll help you get the food.

461
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:26,059
No, but Professor Fan needs someone...

462
00:15:26,340 --> 00:15:27,179
Sitting and chatting

463
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,779
isn't as good as getting up and moving.

464
00:15:28,899 --> 00:15:29,659
Let's go together.

465
00:15:29,659 --> 00:15:30,379
Let's go.

466
00:15:31,220 --> 00:15:32,539
The person taking care of him will be here soon.

467
00:15:32,799 --> 00:15:34,240
I can't be without someone taking care of me.

468
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:36,399
Is it Zhu Zhu or Xiao Xin? Who is it?

469
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:39,620
Xiao Cai.

470
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:41,580
Xiao Cai, why is it you?

471
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:43,899
I just met some college students at the door,

472
00:15:43,899 --> 00:15:45,580
so I took the food from them.

473
00:15:45,580 --> 00:15:46,299
Boss Li.

474
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,460
Guess what's in my bowl?

475
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:51,539
I brought you some sheep liver.

476
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:53,139
There's really sheep liver?

477
00:15:53,139 --> 00:15:54,259
Isn't it a coincidence?

478
00:15:54,419 --> 00:15:56,220
The cafeteria is serving sheep liver today.

479
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:58,019
Come, open your mouth. It's good for your eyes.

480
00:15:58,019 --> 00:15:58,779
I'm not eating it.

481
00:15:58,820 --> 00:15:59,740
It's good for your eyes.

482
00:16:00,019 --> 00:16:01,460
If you don't eat, you'll go blind.

483
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,659
Hurry up, open your mouth.

484
00:16:17,019 --> 00:16:18,620
What time is it now?

485
00:16:20,059 --> 00:16:22,340
Time for my water and medicine, right?

486
00:16:23,419 --> 00:16:24,460
Medicine, huh?

487
00:16:24,779 --> 00:16:25,500
Here.

488
00:16:25,659 --> 00:16:26,700
I'll feed you.

489
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:27,779
Who asked you to feed me?

490
00:16:28,860 --> 00:16:30,659
I want Ms. Liu.

491
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:32,100
Ms. Liu?

492
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:34,419
She can't come.

493
00:16:35,039 --> 00:16:35,879
How come she...

494
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,500
How do you know she can't come?

495
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:39,879
Of course I know.

496
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,360
I told her not to come.

497
00:16:41,879 --> 00:16:42,960
How could you?

498
00:16:44,039 --> 00:16:45,879
I'm sick as a dog here.

499
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,519
Come on, Old Fan.

500
00:16:49,879 --> 00:16:51,480
A minor headache and fever.

501
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:53,440
You've been lying there for days.

502
00:16:53,879 --> 00:16:55,200
I've figured it out.

503
00:16:55,879 --> 00:16:57,279
As long as Ms. Liu doesn't come,

504
00:16:57,919 --> 00:16:58,759
this illness of yours

505
00:16:59,559 --> 00:17:00,519
will be cured instantly.

506
00:17:00,559 --> 00:17:01,799
What do you mean?

507
00:17:02,159 --> 00:17:02,960
What do I mean?

508
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:05,680
Since we're on the subject,

509
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,279
I'd like to ask you.

510
00:17:09,799 --> 00:17:11,480
Ms. Liu coming to take care of you,

511
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:15,359
is it out of pure concern for a comrade?

512
00:17:15,839 --> 00:17:18,880
Is it out of pure patriotism?

513
00:17:19,279 --> 00:17:20,859
Is it out of a sincere

514
00:17:20,859 --> 00:17:22,880
belief in saving lives?

515
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:23,720
In his fifties,

516
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,200
he traveled thousands of miles to China.

517
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:25,859
Stop.

518
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,359
You...

519
00:17:26,359 --> 00:17:27,960
Are you talking about Ms. Liu?

520
00:17:29,599 --> 00:17:30,519
That's Norman Bethune.

521
00:17:31,359 --> 00:17:32,160
Same thing.

522
00:17:33,759 --> 00:17:35,700
Ms. Liu inherited Comrade Norman Bethune's

523
00:17:35,799 --> 00:17:37,700
fearlessness of hardship, filth, and fatigue,

524
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:39,000
and the spirit of not fearing stench.

525
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,000
How am I smelly?

526
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,759
That's why she came to care for you.

527
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,920
And as for your behavior,

528
00:17:44,519 --> 00:17:46,599
can you be called a noble person?

529
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,759
A pure person?

530
00:17:49,519 --> 00:17:51,460
Can you be called a person with moral integrity?

531
00:17:51,980 --> 00:17:53,200
Can you be called a person

532
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,480
who is free from vulgar interests?

533
00:17:56,279 --> 00:17:58,799
Simply a wolf's ambition!

534
00:17:58,799 --> 00:17:59,880
A beast in human clothing!

535
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:00,720
Shut your mouth!

536
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:03,559
What did I do?

537
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:05,779
You're dumping all these

538
00:18:05,779 --> 00:18:07,500
shit basins and piss pots,

539
00:18:07,660 --> 00:18:09,180
foot-binding cloths and smelly socks on me.

540
00:18:09,180 --> 00:18:10,220
No, as for what you did,

541
00:18:10,220 --> 00:18:11,400
don't you know yourself?

542
00:18:12,420 --> 00:18:14,380
You intentionally sent me away multiple times.

543
00:18:14,380 --> 00:18:14,920
Didn't you?

544
00:18:15,099 --> 00:18:15,779
To create

545
00:18:15,779 --> 00:18:18,299
opportunities for you and Ms. Liu to be alone.

546
00:18:18,299 --> 00:18:18,859
Didn't you?

547
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:21,339
To achieve your ulterior motives.

548
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,180
Didn't you?

549
00:18:23,660 --> 00:18:25,180
What motives?

550
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,660
Old Li, let me tell you.

551
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:28,700
If we're talking about

552
00:18:29,019 --> 00:18:29,900
having motives,

553
00:18:30,220 --> 00:18:31,420
it's Ms. Liu who

554
00:18:32,299 --> 00:18:33,660
has motives towards me.

555
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:36,380
Ridiculous.

556
00:18:36,619 --> 00:18:37,660
That is just too ridiculous.

557
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:39,380
You're turning it around on her?

558
00:18:39,779 --> 00:18:40,859
You didn't expect that, did you?

559
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:41,740
I didn't.

560
00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:43,619
During the time I sent you away,

561
00:18:43,619 --> 00:18:45,059
in those bits and pieces of time,

562
00:18:45,980 --> 00:18:46,539
Ms. Liu

563
00:18:47,019 --> 00:18:48,180
has already

564
00:18:48,299 --> 00:18:49,259
expressed

565
00:18:49,579 --> 00:18:50,420
that intention to me.

566
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:51,660
What intention?

567
00:18:51,660 --> 00:18:52,259
You're making it up.

568
00:18:52,420 --> 00:18:53,400
You can really spin a yarn.

569
00:18:53,859 --> 00:18:54,660
I don't believe it.

570
00:18:54,819 --> 00:18:55,660
Not a single word.

571
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:57,140
Believe it or not.

572
00:18:57,619 --> 00:18:59,019
You have no choice but to believe.

573
00:19:00,259 --> 00:19:01,559
Ms. Liu said it herself.

574
00:19:02,059 --> 00:19:03,099
That I, Fan,

575
00:19:03,420 --> 00:19:05,099
am learned, talented, and highly respected.

576
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:07,660
That I dedicated my heart and talent

577
00:19:08,180 --> 00:19:09,940
to the next generation.

578
00:19:10,259 --> 00:19:11,339
In her heart,

579
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,059
I am the one she respects and admires most.

580
00:19:13,059 --> 00:19:14,619
The most lovable person!

581
00:19:16,039 --> 00:19:17,259
The one she likes is me,

582
00:19:17,559 --> 00:19:18,400
Fan himself.

583
00:19:21,319 --> 00:19:22,660
Stop being so gross

584
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,640
That holy, upright, and aloof

585
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,539
Ms. Liu

586
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:28,099
how could she say such mushy things?

587
00:19:28,339 --> 00:19:30,660
But she just had to go and say them.

588
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:32,259
In front of a patient.

589
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:33,700
She opened her heart.

590
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,180
No longer hiding anything.

591
00:19:35,180 --> 00:19:35,680
You're making it up.

592
00:19:36,119 --> 00:19:36,579
You're bragging.

593
00:19:36,579 --> 00:19:37,519
Actually,

594
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:38,940
getting sick

595
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:41,059
isn't anything to be happy about.

596
00:19:41,660 --> 00:19:44,019
But it's a blessing in disguise.

597
00:19:44,519 --> 00:19:46,279
I have to thank this illness.

598
00:19:46,279 --> 00:19:48,240
It's good that I caught this cold.

599
00:19:50,039 --> 00:19:51,240
You know, Old Li?

600
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,799
Being fit and never getting sick,

601
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:54,880
sometimes,

602
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,960
isn't necessarily a good thing.

603
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:04,480
Come in.

604
00:20:05,039 --> 00:20:05,839
Xiao Cai.

605
00:20:07,759 --> 00:20:08,640
Professor Fan.

606
00:20:09,039 --> 00:20:09,759
Come.

607
00:20:09,759 --> 00:20:10,960
Watching TV?

608
00:20:11,019 --> 00:20:12,019
Have a seat.

609
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:12,900
Sit here.

610
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:19,859
What are you holding there?

611
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:20,759
No...

612
00:20:20,759 --> 00:20:21,500
nothing.

613
00:20:26,519 --> 00:20:27,660
What are you doing?

614
00:20:27,819 --> 00:20:29,420
Playing hide-and-seek with us?

615
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:31,200
It's nothing.

616
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:31,960
It's just...

617
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:35,519
Such beautiful flowers.

618
00:20:37,079 --> 00:20:38,240
They smell quite nice too.

619
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:38,960
Right?

620
00:20:39,119 --> 00:20:40,240
I know this flower.

621
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:41,059
You know it?

622
00:20:41,839 --> 00:20:42,940
This flower is called...

623
00:20:43,220 --> 00:20:44,279
Carnation.

624
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,240
Thank you.

625
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,759
What carnation?

626
00:20:47,759 --> 00:20:49,480
Carnations are for mothers.

627
00:20:49,799 --> 00:20:50,799
What are you thanking me for?

628
00:20:50,799 --> 00:20:51,720
No, these flowers...

629
00:20:51,799 --> 00:20:53,519
I'm giving them to Ms. Liu.

630
00:20:53,839 --> 00:20:54,880
For Ms. Liu?

631
00:20:55,799 --> 00:20:56,839
Not for me?

632
00:20:56,839 --> 00:20:57,599
Sorry.

633
00:20:57,799 --> 00:20:58,900
So they aren't for you.

634
00:21:00,119 --> 00:21:01,180
But...

635
00:21:01,299 --> 00:21:04,160
isn't it inappropriate to give Ms. Liu carnations?

636
00:21:04,539 --> 00:21:05,880
This isn't a carnation.

637
00:21:06,259 --> 00:21:07,380
Then what flower is it?

638
00:21:09,019 --> 00:21:10,220
I'm not too sure either.

639
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:12,619
Where is Ms. Liu?

640
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,059
She'll be back in a moment.

641
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:17,420
Professor Fan.

642
00:21:19,359 --> 00:21:20,039
Um...

643
00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:22,599
You coming here today...

644
00:21:22,599 --> 00:21:24,599
is there some other meaning behind it?

645
00:21:25,839 --> 00:21:27,440
What other meaning could I have?

646
00:21:27,519 --> 00:21:28,519
I just came to...

647
00:21:28,839 --> 00:21:30,960
express my gratitude to Ms. Liu.

648
00:21:32,359 --> 00:21:33,400
Keep it a secret, okay?

649
00:21:34,079 --> 00:21:35,039
Express gratitude?

650
00:21:35,039 --> 00:21:36,519
Why keep it a secret?

651
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:39,079
Professor Fan.

652
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:40,720
Look.

653
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:42,380
I just said it and Ms. Liu is back.

654
00:21:42,839 --> 00:21:44,440
Hurry up.

655
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:44,960
What's wrong?

656
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:46,619
Professor Fan has been waiting for you for ages.

657
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:47,099
Waiting for me?

658
00:21:47,099 --> 00:21:48,440
He's been dying to give you flowers.

659
00:21:48,559 --> 00:21:50,200
To express gratitude, and keep it secret.

660
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:51,640
I'm going out.

661
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,599
Don't go out...

662
00:21:53,599 --> 00:21:54,240
Don't...

663
00:21:54,519 --> 00:21:54,980
Um...

664
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:56,799
Don't, don't stop.

665
00:21:56,799 --> 00:21:59,000
Go take care of any urgent business you have.

666
00:21:59,359 --> 00:22:00,039
And...

667
00:22:00,599 --> 00:22:01,839
no rush to come back.

668
00:22:02,119 --> 00:22:03,200
I know.

669
00:22:14,319 --> 00:22:14,920
Um,

670
00:22:15,160 --> 00:22:16,319
Please sit, Professor Fan.

671
00:22:16,319 --> 00:22:16,920
Um,

672
00:22:18,559 --> 00:22:19,359
Ms. Liu.

673
00:22:20,079 --> 00:22:22,559
I've put you to so much trouble these past few days.

674
00:22:22,759 --> 00:22:23,839
I came to thank you.

675
00:22:26,559 --> 00:22:27,640
Here are some flowers for you.

676
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:28,220
No...

677
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:29,279
Not you...

678
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:31,000
Why are you being so polite?

679
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:31,339
No...

680
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:32,619
Professor Fan, this...

681
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,240
These flowers...

682
00:22:35,039 --> 00:22:36,400
You bought the wrong ones.

683
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:37,680
Wrong?

684
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:38,759
How are they wrong?

685
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,559
These are roses.

686
00:22:42,839 --> 00:22:44,200
It's not appropriate for you to give me these.

687
00:22:44,839 --> 00:22:46,160
If you wanted to give me flowers,

688
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:47,039
you should have given...

689
00:22:47,319 --> 00:22:48,200
yellow lilies,

690
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,559
or daffodils.

691
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,359
Those are for thanking good friends.

692
00:22:52,519 --> 00:22:53,259
But these flowers...

693
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:54,960
This...

694
00:22:55,359 --> 00:22:56,119
This...

695
00:22:56,119 --> 00:22:58,160
Have you never studied the language of flowers?

696
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:59,960
How could I not have studied flowers?

697
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:01,319
Right.

698
00:23:01,319 --> 00:23:02,759
I haven't studied it.

699
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,680
I just thought these flowers were pretty,

700
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:05,960
so I just bought them.

701
00:23:07,119 --> 00:23:08,000
I'm sorry, Ms. Liu.

702
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,119
Please don't mind.

703
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:10,299
No...

704
00:23:10,359 --> 00:23:11,079
Really.

705
00:23:11,079 --> 00:23:12,720
I should thank you.

706
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:15,039
Because for so many years,

707
00:23:17,559 --> 00:23:19,559
no one has given me such...

708
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,000
such beautiful flowers.

709
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:21,960
I only...

710
00:23:22,359 --> 00:23:24,039
did such a small thing,

711
00:23:24,559 --> 00:23:26,200
and you gave me such beautiful flowers.

712
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,359
I'm simply...

713
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:28,720
How about this?

714
00:23:29,079 --> 00:23:30,599
I'll treat you to a meal later.

715
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:33,880
That would be great.

716
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:35,759
No.

717
00:23:36,279 --> 00:23:37,720
I'll treat you to a meal.

718
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:38,799
What would you like to eat?

719
00:23:38,799 --> 00:23:40,039
Order whatever you want.

720
00:23:41,759 --> 00:23:42,099
Xiao Cai!

721
00:23:42,099 --> 00:23:43,099
It's terrible!

722
00:23:43,099 --> 00:23:44,099
Xiao Cai,

723
00:23:44,099 --> 00:23:45,240
why are you back again?

724
00:23:45,279 --> 00:23:46,059
Didn't I tell you,

725
00:23:46,059 --> 00:23:47,539
there's no rush to come back?

726
00:23:47,539 --> 00:23:48,559
I know.

727
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:50,059
But I have something urgent.

728
00:23:50,059 --> 00:23:51,380
No matter how urgent, it's not as...

729
00:23:51,380 --> 00:23:52,519
This *is* urgent!

730
00:23:52,599 --> 00:23:54,400
I mean, haven't you finished your business yet?

731
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:55,460
Hurry up and go, go on.

732
00:23:55,460 --> 00:23:55,900
Go handle it.

733
00:23:55,900 --> 00:23:57,119
What do you mean "go"?

734
00:23:57,160 --> 00:23:58,500
Let me finish what I'm saying!

735
00:23:58,579 --> 00:24:00,059
Boss Li, Li Jianguo...

736
00:24:00,119 --> 00:24:01,339
he's sick again.

737
00:24:02,839 --> 00:24:03,640
Oh my heavens.

738
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:04,700
I'll go take a look.
